# Subscriptions

Panels return **different bodies per User-Agent**. Never use default Dart `http` UA.

## UA selection (`ConfigParser._subscriptionUserAgent`)

| Engine | User-Agent | Response shape |
|--------|------------|----------------|
| xray | `v2rayNG/1.8.29` | JSON array of xray configs |
| singbox | `sing-box` | Base64 → newline-separated links |

Always send `Accept-Encoding: identity`.

## Normalization pipeline

1. Try base64 decode of body
2. If `[` → `_selectV2rayNgConfig` (skip decoy entries)
3. If `{` → raw JSON (rare on desktop; sanitize heavily)
4. Else → first non-decoy config link per line

## Post-processing (`injectSecureSocksInbound`)

- xray: `_normalizeXraySubscriptionConfig` — rewrite `proxy` outbound tag, drop `api` rules
- singbox: `_migrateSingboxLegacyDns`
- desktop: `proxyOnly: true` — strip all inbounds, add secure SOCKS only

## Adding a new panel format

1. Document UA + sample body in `troubleshooting.md`
2. Extend `normalizeSubscriptionContent` with detection branch
3. Add fixture test in `config_parser_test.dart` (synthetic JSON, no live URLs)
